WEBVTT

00:02.670 --> 00:03.880
Dre: In my family,
between the giant age range

00:03.880 --> 00:05.120
and all our different
interests...

00:05.120 --> 00:06.670
♪♪

00:06.670 --> 00:07.710
[ Sniffs ]

00:07.710 --> 00:09.750
♪♪

00:11.790 --> 00:15.670
Nice!
That was my card!

00:15.670 --> 00:18.790
...it's hard to find
a game we can all play.

00:18.790 --> 00:19.790
Mount Rushmore!

00:19.790 --> 00:20.790
A cloud?

00:20.790 --> 00:21.790
A-An amoeba?

00:21.790 --> 00:22.790
Madagascar!

00:22.790 --> 00:24.040
O-Oh, a blob!

00:24.040 --> 00:25.000
Texas!
[ Bell dings ]

00:25.000 --> 00:27.040
What?
It's a ghost!

00:27.040 --> 00:28.210
Get her!
Get her!

00:28.210 --> 00:29.830
What are you --
Oh, my God.
Get her!

00:29.830 --> 00:32.380
So when I want to get everyone
together for game night,

00:32.380 --> 00:34.460
I have to bring out
the big dog --

00:34.460 --> 00:36.250
"Monopoly."

00:36.250 --> 00:37.750
Aside from chess and checkers,

00:37.750 --> 00:40.420
it's the most popular game
on earth.

00:40.420 --> 00:43.540
"Monopoly" is life.
Hold up.

00:43.540 --> 00:46.120
That's confusing
since "Life" is also a game.

00:46.120 --> 00:48.170
The point is, with "Monopoly,"

00:48.170 --> 00:50.290
how you play reveals
who you are.

00:50.290 --> 00:52.790
For example,
Diane is a killer.

00:52.790 --> 00:54.460
Guys!
Game time!

00:54.460 --> 00:56.710
And Jack is never
gonna make it.

01:02.080 --> 01:06.000
Just like in life, "Monopoly's"
all about who you team up with

01:06.000 --> 01:08.500
and Bow and I are inseparable.

01:08.500 --> 01:09.330
We got the shoe?

01:09.330 --> 01:10.830
You know it.
[ Laughs ]

01:10.830 --> 01:13.830
Because only weirdos
are wheelbarrows.

01:13.830 --> 01:17.080
Oh, God,
I love game night.
Mm-hmm.

01:17.080 --> 01:19.620
We get to be all cozy,
just family.

01:19.620 --> 01:20.620
Hey, guys!
Hi.

01:20.620 --> 01:21.750
Hey.

01:21.750 --> 01:23.380
...and an interloper
no one likes.

01:23.380 --> 01:25.290
Ooh!
I call the wheelbarrow.

01:25.290 --> 01:27.500
Hi, Dr. Johnson,
Mr. Johnson.

01:27.500 --> 01:28.580
I brought you some wine.

01:28.580 --> 01:30.790
Oh, how nice.

01:30.790 --> 01:32.120
How rude.

01:32.120 --> 01:33.330
We could be alcoholics.
She don't know.

01:33.330 --> 01:34.380
Be nice.

01:34.380 --> 01:36.580
Thank you.
Yes, thank you,

01:36.580 --> 01:39.790
minor with alcohol,
roping us in to your felony.

01:39.790 --> 01:41.000
[ Chuckles ]

01:41.000 --> 01:42.830
Hey, Megan.
What's up?

01:42.830 --> 01:45.080
We're the dog.
Don't even try.

01:45.080 --> 01:46.420
Rainbow:
Oh. Diane.

01:46.420 --> 01:49.040
Since there are so many of us,
we play with partners, so...

01:49.040 --> 01:51.250
She's the brain,
I'm the hands.

01:51.250 --> 01:54.080
And we are
an established partnership...

01:54.080 --> 01:55.290
Mm-hmm.
...not some
high-school fling.

01:55.290 --> 01:57.880
Oh, and remember,
this is about fun.

01:57.880 --> 01:59.080
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

01:59.080 --> 02:00.380
And winning.
Sure.

02:00.380 --> 02:01.540
Fun and winning.

02:01.540 --> 02:03.170
Whatever helps
you sleep at night, babe.

02:03.170 --> 02:04.960
Well, nobody sleeps
better than a winner.

02:04.960 --> 02:07.830
Uh, Dad is obsessed with winning
because he never does.

02:07.830 --> 02:09.460
They do.

02:09.460 --> 02:11.790
[ DMX's "Where the Hood At"
plays ]

02:11.790 --> 02:14.380
♪ Where the hood, where the
hood, where the hood at ♪

02:14.380 --> 02:16.920
♪ Have that...in the cut,
where the wood at? ♪

02:16.920 --> 02:19.080
♪ Dee, waah, unh ♪
Unh!

02:19.080 --> 02:20.920
Looking good,
Mrs. Johnson.

02:20.920 --> 02:22.080
Back at you,
Mr. Johnson.

02:22.080 --> 02:23.120
Come on. Let's get it.
Hey!

02:23.120 --> 02:25.210
Yo! Mm-hmm.
Unh-unh.

02:25.210 --> 02:26.500
I thought
they were divorced.

02:26.500 --> 02:27.830
Oh, we are.
Violently so.

02:27.830 --> 02:30.620
Yeah. You see, this nightmare
of a man ruined my life,

02:30.620 --> 02:33.330
but I wouldn't have anybody else
as my "Monopoly" partner.

02:33.330 --> 02:34.580
Hey!

02:34.580 --> 02:36.170
They are ruthless.

02:36.170 --> 02:38.500
Hey, hey, it's just a friendly
family game, Junior.
Uh-huh.

02:39.880 --> 02:41.040
Everybody,
$10 on the Free Parking.

02:41.040 --> 02:42.290
You know the rules.

02:42.290 --> 02:43.670
-Here we go.
-Give it up, give it up.

02:43.670 --> 02:45.540
Give it up, give it up.
-I've never heard of that.

02:45.540 --> 02:46.460
See, in my family --

02:46.460 --> 02:47.670
No one cares what you do.

02:47.670 --> 02:49.250
This is "Black Monopoly,"

02:49.250 --> 02:50.580
so let me break down
the rules for you, all right?

02:50.580 --> 02:52.290
No side-coaching...
Mnh-mnh.

02:52.290 --> 02:53.670
...no gifting of money...
Mnh-mnh.

02:53.670 --> 02:55.080
...but loans
are allowed.

02:55.080 --> 02:57.080
Just know you're never
gonna get your money back.

02:57.080 --> 02:59.620
You cannot collect rent
while you're in jail...
Yep.

02:59.620 --> 03:01.580
...and Pops does not
pay income tax.

03:01.580 --> 03:02.790
Reparations.

03:02.790 --> 03:04.750
And do not forget

03:04.750 --> 03:07.540
about the Andre Johnson
Man Baby Tax.

03:07.540 --> 03:09.250
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Junior: Oh!

03:09.250 --> 03:10.670
If you lose your temper

03:10.670 --> 03:12.710
and you flip the board...
Ruby: Mm-hmm.

03:12.710 --> 03:14.960
...you owe everyone
an actual $100.

03:14.960 --> 03:16.500
Diane: Yep.
Uh-huh.

03:16.500 --> 03:20.330
I got this scar from a flying
top hat hitting me in 2015.

03:20.330 --> 03:21.710
Ooh.

03:21.710 --> 03:24.290
But I got paid, though,
you know what I'm saying?

03:24.290 --> 03:25.380
[ Indistinct chatter ]
Green money!

03:25.380 --> 03:26.670
Green money!

03:26.670 --> 03:29.080
Let's play.
Let's do it!

03:29.080 --> 03:30.500
♪ My baby don't mess around ♪
-All right.
-All right!

03:30.500 --> 03:32.380
-Listen up.
-Yes!

03:32.380 --> 03:35.000
♪ Because she loves me so,
and this I know fo sho ♪
[ All cheering ]

03:35.000 --> 03:36.750
1, 2, 3, 4!
Yeah!

03:36.750 --> 03:38.210
Hey, move me!

03:38.210 --> 03:39.670
♪ But does she really want to ♪
Hey, that was crazy!

03:39.670 --> 03:41.000
♪ But can't stand to see me ♪
[ Laughs ]

03:41.000 --> 03:42.580
♪ Walk out the door? ♪
Diane: All right,
all right, all right.

03:42.580 --> 03:44.210
Aah!

03:45.210 --> 03:46.420
♪ Shake it, sh-shake it ♪
Oh!

03:46.420 --> 03:49.210
Okay.
Okay. Okay.

03:49.210 --> 03:50.420
♪ Shake it, sh-shake it ♪
All: Ohh!

03:50.420 --> 03:53.120
Come on.
Give me 5 to stay alive.

03:53.120 --> 03:54.170
♪ Like a Polaroid picture ♪

03:54.170 --> 03:55.960
Hey!
♪ Hey ya ♪

03:55.960 --> 03:58.290
[ Dice clacking ]

03:58.290 --> 04:00.380
♪ Hey ♪
[ Music stops ]

04:00.380 --> 04:03.210
[ Clacking continues ]

04:03.210 --> 04:06.580
Okay.

04:14.330 --> 04:15.880
This is why
people hate you.

04:15.880 --> 04:17.080
Okay. Okay.

04:17.080 --> 04:19.250
[ Dice clatter ]
Oh.

04:19.250 --> 04:20.290
Can I get another try,
just --

04:20.290 --> 04:21.290
No!
No!

04:21.290 --> 04:23.250
[ Ding! ]

04:23.250 --> 04:25.620
Mm, mm, mm, mm.
Yes!

04:25.620 --> 04:27.920
All right. All right,
come on, Community Chest!

04:27.920 --> 04:29.290
Okay. Okay.
Talk to me.

04:29.290 --> 04:31.250
"You've won second prize
in a beauty contest.

04:31.250 --> 04:32.580
[Singsong voice]
Collect $10!"

04:32.580 --> 04:35.460
Can't even come in first
in a made-up contest.

04:35.460 --> 04:36.960
Okay,
I'm still very much

04:36.960 --> 04:38.250
younger than you
in real life.
Baby.

04:38.250 --> 04:39.330
All right, all right.
So...
Shh.

04:39.330 --> 04:42.380
Ooh.
1, 2, collect $200.

04:42.380 --> 04:43.960
$200!

04:43.960 --> 04:45.710
3, 4...Baltic.
We'll take it.

04:45.710 --> 04:49.080
Oh, statistically speaking,
I wouldn't do that.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.750
Unless you own four houses,

04:50.750 --> 04:53.880
Baltic and Mediterranean
is a terrible investment.

04:53.880 --> 04:56.080
Uh, statistically speaking,
Junior,

04:56.080 --> 04:58.040
you need
to shut [bleep] up.

04:58.040 --> 04:59.080
[ Ruby laughs ]

04:59.080 --> 05:02.080
Give me $60.
[ Laughing ] All right.

05:02.080 --> 05:05.000
Hey.
When did I have cashews?

05:05.000 --> 05:07.120
Ah, 1, 2, 3, 4.
Unh, unh, unh, unh.

05:07.120 --> 05:08.540
Kentucky Avenue!
Ooh!

05:08.540 --> 05:10.170
[ As Foghorn Leghorn ]
Oh, I say, I say,

05:10.170 --> 05:13.460
you owe me $18 for Kentucky,
sir.

05:13.460 --> 05:15.380
...3, 4.

05:15.380 --> 05:17.420
[ Brooklyn accent ]
$200 for New York Avenue?

05:17.420 --> 05:18.830
[ Brooklyn accent ]
Forget about it!

05:18.830 --> 05:20.460
Okay.
Unh, unh, unh.

05:20.460 --> 05:21.830
St. Charles Place.

05:21.830 --> 05:22.960
Who owns that?

05:22.960 --> 05:24.620
[ Jamaican accent ]
Hey, mon. Pay me now.

05:24.620 --> 05:27.460
Lord, have mercy.
What you think this is?

05:27.460 --> 05:28.330
Shabba!

05:33.420 --> 05:36.670
[ Normal voice ] I'm sorry.
My family went to Sandals.

05:36.670 --> 05:39.040
[ Groans ]

05:40.750 --> 05:41.880
Okay.
Yes!

05:41.880 --> 05:43.420
That's your third
double!

05:43.420 --> 05:44.790
[ Laughs ]
[ Normal voice ] No!

05:44.790 --> 05:46.540
Can't go to jail again.

05:46.540 --> 05:47.580
Oh, it's okay, honey.

05:47.580 --> 05:48.620
I will sell you

05:48.620 --> 05:50.540
my Get Out of Jail Free card
for a dollar.

05:50.540 --> 05:52.170
Wait.
We don't need her help.

05:52.170 --> 05:53.920
Why don't you just take it,
honey?

05:53.920 --> 05:55.330
Let's win on our own.

05:56.750 --> 05:58.000
You know what?

05:58.000 --> 05:59.330
Mom,
I don't need your help.

05:59.330 --> 06:01.460
What?
You know my girl.

06:01.460 --> 06:03.790
She got me while
I'm serving my nickel.

06:03.790 --> 06:05.250
Gonna put money
on my books.

06:05.250 --> 06:08.250
-Yuck.
-Ain't that right, boo?

06:08.250 --> 06:10.120
I'm scared to say anything
this time.

06:10.120 --> 06:11.460
[ Baby crying ]
You know what?

06:11.460 --> 06:12.920
Okay. I will be right back.
Keep playing without me.

06:12.920 --> 06:14.500
[ Dice clatter ]
You sure?

06:14.500 --> 06:16.000
You know,
I'm happy to wait.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.830
Means less if you roll
before you say it, Dre!

06:18.830 --> 06:20.120
New York!
We own it.

06:20.120 --> 06:23.250
Oh, sorry.
No rent for jailbirds.

06:23.250 --> 06:25.330
That's white justice.

06:25.330 --> 06:26.540
[ Laughs ]

06:28.580 --> 06:30.420
Oh!
Another double!

06:30.420 --> 06:33.460
Suddenly, with Bow gone,
I could feel my luck changing.

06:33.460 --> 06:36.080
Marvin's Garden!

06:36.080 --> 06:37.170
Uh-huh.
I'll take it.

06:37.170 --> 06:39.920
Dad,
it's Marvin Gardens.

06:39.920 --> 06:42.330
$20 change, please.
Not Marvin's Garden.

06:42.330 --> 06:44.040
It's like
it's not Olive's Garden.

06:44.040 --> 06:46.670
You talkin' 'bout how my baby
loves Olive's Garden?

06:46.670 --> 06:50.460
Y'all are just jealous because
I got the first Monopoly.

06:50.460 --> 06:51.710
Oh, we got a Monopoly?

06:51.710 --> 06:54.500
No, I got a Monopoly,
Albatross.

06:54.500 --> 06:55.920
What?

06:55.920 --> 06:58.330
You know, now I'm finally
starting to understand

06:58.330 --> 07:00.380
why I always lose.

07:00.380 --> 07:01.790
Why?
'Cause you're bad at this?

07:03.580 --> 07:05.380
Children, how about I give you
Vermont Avenue...

07:05.380 --> 07:06.380
What?

07:06.380 --> 07:07.620
...and $100...

07:07.620 --> 07:08.620
No!

07:08.620 --> 07:09.540
...if you take Mommy
on your team.

07:09.540 --> 07:11.080
Wha--

07:11.080 --> 07:14.710
$200, and you agree
not to have any more children.

07:14.710 --> 07:16.460
Okay, that's a decision
I have -- no.
Deal.

07:16.460 --> 07:17.920
Deal.
No. No, okay.

07:17.920 --> 07:19.880
Jack: Thank you.
I don't know
what is going on here.

07:19.880 --> 07:22.500
What's going on?
That's exactly
why I sold you.

07:22.500 --> 07:24.120
You sold me?
Uh-huh.

07:24.120 --> 07:25.790
Now, please, go on.
Get up over there.
Your team awaits.

07:25.790 --> 07:28.920
Oh...my...God.
Your team awaits.

07:28.920 --> 07:32.620
It's time for Daddy to shine
because this couch is all mine.

07:32.620 --> 07:33.920
Wow. Okay. Sure.
[ Laughs ]

07:37.960 --> 07:39.080
So, I'm finally living

07:39.080 --> 07:40.170
now that something
has separated me and Bow --

07:40.170 --> 07:41.170
me.

07:41.170 --> 07:42.710
Let me squeeze in.

07:42.710 --> 07:43.790
Mom.
Okay.

07:43.790 --> 07:44.830
Hold on.
Help me in, then.
Aah!

07:44.830 --> 07:46.710
Ooh.
I got it.

07:46.710 --> 07:48.540
Ugh.
Damn velour.

07:48.540 --> 07:49.750
Doesn't breathe.

07:49.750 --> 07:51.960
We never should have changed
what worked.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.210
♪ Won on you ♪

07:53.210 --> 07:55.120
♪ We won on you, we won ♪

07:55.120 --> 07:58.790
♪ Won, won, won-won,
won, won-won, won, won ♪

07:58.790 --> 08:00.960
I loved those suits.

08:00.960 --> 08:03.120
I never would have
blown your boat up

08:03.120 --> 08:05.420
if I knew those suits
were on it.

08:05.420 --> 08:06.830
I'm gonna go
to the bathroom.
Okay.

08:06.830 --> 08:09.920
Jack, don't make any deals
or trades without me.

08:09.920 --> 08:11.380
Understand?
Okay. All right.

08:13.170 --> 08:15.040
Hey, Jack.

08:15.040 --> 08:17.960
How about I trade you Short Line
for Pacific Avenue?

08:17.960 --> 08:20.330
Uh,
Diane said no trades.

08:20.330 --> 08:23.330
Okay, how about
you give me that one,

08:23.330 --> 08:25.880
and I'll give you this one?

08:25.880 --> 08:27.960
Oh.
A give-and-give!

08:27.960 --> 08:28.960
Mm-hmm.
Sure.

08:28.960 --> 08:30.500
No, no!
Don't do it.

08:30.500 --> 08:31.960
Hey, no side-coaching.

08:31.960 --> 08:33.290
Sweetheart,
it's not a good trade.

08:33.290 --> 08:35.830
No side-coaching!

08:35.830 --> 08:39.540
I'm on his team now.

08:39.540 --> 08:41.330
Statistically,
Short Line is worthless

08:41.330 --> 08:42.880
without the other three
railroads,

08:42.880 --> 08:44.380
and you don't have them.

08:44.380 --> 08:47.750
Now, maybe Grandma and Pops,
they'll sell theirs to you.

08:47.750 --> 08:49.460
Stop lyin' to the boy.

08:49.460 --> 08:52.290
You know we never go easy
on anybody.

08:52.290 --> 08:55.420
We want our money, man!

08:55.420 --> 08:57.920
Ruby:
I swear to God, little boy!

08:57.920 --> 08:59.750
Okay.

08:59.750 --> 09:01.620
[ Whispers ] Hey, Jack.

09:01.620 --> 09:03.540
[ Normal voice ] You just do
what you think is right,

09:03.540 --> 09:05.920
and everyone
will respect you for it.

09:05.920 --> 09:07.210
Okay?

09:07.210 --> 09:09.120
Jack.

09:09.120 --> 09:11.380
You know what
the right thing to do is.

09:11.380 --> 09:12.920
Think, honey.

09:12.920 --> 09:15.040
♪♪

09:15.040 --> 09:15.880
Let's trade.

09:15.880 --> 09:17.580
Aw, man!
[ Laughs ]

09:18.500 --> 09:19.580
Dumb baby.

09:19.580 --> 09:21.040
Dad!
Dre.

09:21.040 --> 09:23.460
He is a dumb baby.
Look. This is my corner.

09:23.460 --> 09:26.170
I own this corner.

09:26.170 --> 09:28.960
Ah!
I am a corner boy!

09:28.960 --> 09:30.460
[ Laughs ]
Diane: What did you do?

09:30.460 --> 09:32.330
You're just the hands.

09:32.330 --> 09:34.460
I'm the brains!

09:34.460 --> 09:35.710
Okay, I'd like three houses,
please.

09:35.710 --> 09:37.380
Oh, Lord.

09:37.380 --> 09:38.670
Are you sure you want
to do that, Dre?

09:38.670 --> 09:40.540
You know, you might
overextend yourself.

09:40.540 --> 09:43.080
You know what?

09:43.080 --> 09:44.460
Give me six more houses.

09:44.460 --> 09:47.170
You can't hold me back anymore.
I got this.

09:47.170 --> 09:48.880
Oh, look at this.
[ Chuckles ]

09:48.880 --> 09:50.670
Look at this.
Uh-huh.

09:50.670 --> 09:54.080
Come to my corner, 'cause
the corner is always open!

09:54.080 --> 09:55.420
Like your mouth.
Mm-hmm.

09:55.420 --> 09:57.290
Come on, now.

09:57.290 --> 09:58.670
Oh, look at that,
look at that.

09:58.670 --> 10:01.420
What you got, Pops?
What you got?
...2, 3.

10:01.420 --> 10:02.420
Yes!

10:02.420 --> 10:03.920
Ohh!

10:03.920 --> 10:05.880
Atlantic.
Damn!

10:05.880 --> 10:08.330
That's $800, old man!
Count it out slowly.

10:08.330 --> 10:10.830
[ Exhales forcefully,
dice clack ]

10:10.830 --> 10:11.920
Uh-huh. Ooh!
Uh-oh. Uh-oh.

10:11.920 --> 10:13.290
This don't look good.

10:13.290 --> 10:15.080
Rainbow: Mnh, mnh, mnh...

10:15.080 --> 10:16.250
No!

10:16.250 --> 10:18.040
Ooh!
Another eight hundy!

10:18.040 --> 10:19.420
You know what?
I'ma come around there,

10:19.420 --> 10:20.920
'cause I want you to put it
in my waistband.

10:20.920 --> 10:22.290
-Come on.
-Don't do that.

10:22.290 --> 10:24.210
Stop acting a fool.
Okay, mama.

10:24.210 --> 10:26.460
Grandma,
will you loan us $200?

10:26.460 --> 10:29.040
We never loan,
we never sell.

10:29.040 --> 10:33.830
What's in the brassiere
stays in the brassiere.

10:33.830 --> 10:35.620
Except for when
you're napping on the couch.

10:35.620 --> 10:37.830
My waistband
is waiting.

10:37.830 --> 10:39.210
Oh, God.

10:39.210 --> 10:40.500
[ Laughs ]

10:40.500 --> 10:41.880
Oh, it's so unappealing.

10:41.880 --> 10:43.250
Here you go, Dre.
Just go.

10:43.250 --> 10:46.540
I'll see you and your mama
on the street.

10:46.540 --> 10:49.500
Get out of here.
Listen, I'm gonna fix this.

10:49.500 --> 10:50.750
Junior.

10:51.830 --> 10:53.620
Can you lend us $200?

10:53.620 --> 10:55.250
Sure.
Oh.

10:55.250 --> 10:57.120
We really shouldn't.

10:57.120 --> 10:59.620
We're saving
for a house on New York.

10:59.620 --> 11:01.960
Oh.
[ Laughs ]

